{
  "texts": [
    "Considering black-box models, MLP models are not easily interpretable.",
    "This means it can be challenging to understand how an MLP arrives at its predictions.",
    "Interpretability is crucial in bio-and medical informatics, where decisions can have significant consequences.",
    "MLPs do not handle missing data well.",
    "This can be a limitation in bio-and medical informatics, where datasets can be incomplete due to various reasons, such as missing data points or unbalanced data [126]."
  ]
}